I"Œ<h2 id="solution">Solution:</h2>

<p>Assuming $n = 2^q$ for some $q \geq 1$, we have</p>

\[\begin{align*}
        T(n) &amp;= k\left[ T\left(\frac{n}{2^1} \right) \right] + f(n) \\\\
        &amp;= k\left[k\left[ T\left(\frac{n}{2^2} \right) \right] + f\left(\frac{n}{2^1}\right) \right] + f(n) \\\\
        &amp;= k\left[k\left[k\left[ T\left(\frac{n}{2^3} \right) \right] + f\left(\frac{n}{2^2} \right] + f\left(\frac{n}{2^1}  \right] + f(n) \\
        &amp;\vdots \\
        &amp;= k^q\left[ T\left(\frac{n}{2^q} \right) \right] + k^{q - 1}f\left(\frac{n}{2^{q - 1}} + k^{q - 2}f\left(\frac{n}{2^{q - 2}} + \cdots + kf\left(\frac{n}{2^1} + f(n) \\\\
        &amp;= k^q(c) + f(n)\left[\sum_{i = 0}^{q - 1} k^i \right] \\\\
        &amp;= k^q(c) + f(n)\left[\frac{k^q - 1}{k - 1} \right] \\\\
        &amp;= k^{\log_2(n)}(c) + f(n)\left[\frac{k^{\log_2(n)} - 1}{k - 1} \right]
    \end{align*}\]

\[\qed\]
